1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a new shape analysis approach that can be applied to various shape features such as boundaries, which is a common problem in computer vision.
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with shape resampling and point set denoising, which are common problems in graphics.
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper proposes a novel description of shape variations and a geometrically relevant dictionary, which are relevant to computational geometry.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a sparse representation to handle shapes with mixed intrinsic dimensionality, which is a common problem in machine learning.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with shape analysis, which is a common problem in multimedia applications such as 3D modeling and animation.
